#In Windows CMD

1) Install Python: version 3.8+
2) Create a Yolo environment: python -m venv yolov8_env
3) Activate the environment: yolov8_env\Scripts\activate
4) Install the necessary dependencies: pip install torch torchvision torchaudio (for CPUs: torchversion:2.3.1, torchvisionversion:0.18.1)
5) Install YOLOv8: pip install ultralytics
6) Add the data folder and the dataset.yaml file under the project folder with the following structure:
yolov8_project/
├── data/
│ ├── images/
│ │ ├── train/
│ │ ├── val/
│ └── labels/
│ ├── train/
│ ├── val/
└── yolov8.yaml
7) Add train.py under the same directory
8) Modify train.py and specify the number of epochs and the batch size (i.e., epochs=100 and batch=4)
9) Run the train with: python train.py or run: yolo train model=yolov8n.pt data=yolov8.yaml epochs=100 imgsz=640 batch=16
